-- TEXT-Vietnam money market review June 30-July 4
-- 
-- Thu Jul 10, 2014 11:25PM EDT
-- None



HANOI, July 11 (Reuters) - The following is data and excerpts translated from an announcement distributed by Vietnam's central bank. Reuters is not responsible for the content.

Information on the banking activities between June 30-July 4. 1- Deposit and lending rates  1.1. Deposit rates: (percent/year) DongNon-term &  1-6 months 6-12 months  12 months  shorter than 1  or longer  month 0.8-1.0 5.0-6.06.0-7.5  7.5-8.3Dollar  Individuals Organisations 1.0 0.25 1.2. Lending rates: (percent/year)  a. Dong lending ratesShort-termMedium, long-term State-owned banks: - For production, trading9.0-10.010.5-11.5   - For agricultural7.0-8.010.0-11.0  production, rural areas, exports, small- and  medium-sized firms, supporting industries, businesses using  high technology   Joint-stock banks: - For production, trading9.5-10.011.0-12.0 - For agricultural   8.0 10.0-12.0 production, rural areas, exports, small- and medium-sized firms, supporting industries, businesses using  high technology   b. Dollar lending  -- State-owned banks  3.0-4.55.5-6.5  -- Joint-stock banks  4.5-6.06.0-7.0  2- Interbank market rates: The average rates on dong loans slightly fell in most terms shorter than one month. The average rate on overnight term edged down 0.07 percentage point from a week earlier to 2.12 percent/year. The average rates of other terms shorter than one month ranged between 2.53-3.45 percent/year. The average rates on dollar loans were on a declining trend on almost all terms. The average rates on terms from one week to one month moved between 0.46-0.62 percent/year, down 0.03-0.18 percentage point from the previous week.  3- The dong/dollar rates quoted by banks during the week were on a declining trend.